DataElement.preferredName: Statistics Analysis Plan Document Version Language Code ISO21090.CD.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A representation, conceptually a document, that is created to convey the statistical analysis plan version structured content to human beings. A coded value specifying the language that the document is written in. EXAMPLE(S): English, German. NOTE(S): Indicates the language in which all (or most) of discrete data elements that make up document are expressed. Distinct from data type attribute ED.languageCode on document version text attribute which expresses language in which document is rendered. Is most important in circumstances where document is not rendered.
